runs.comm: around the wicket, forward on the stumps and blocked
forward again and flicked out through midwicket for just a single, good deep fielding
down the track and clipped with the turn through square leg for a single
leg stump line, pushed through midwicket and Morgan does very well to save two running back
more off stump line, blocked into point
steps to leg and drives hard into the off side and it goes straight through point, a complete miss from Chris Jordan at point, awful fielding, ruins a good first over
full just outside off, played forward and ran into the covers
off stump line, forward and guided down to third man
full on the stumps, driven down the ground, a good enough connection to clear mid-on and it skips away for four, decent stroke
full on leg stump, clipped through square leg and Jordan this time is able to field successfully so they just get a single
good length on off stump, Williamson forward to block it carefully
similar delivery, this time Williamson opens the face and guides it down to third man
length ball, Williamson went to tuck it to leg and got struck on the pad
steps to leg and slaps a length ball past extra cover, lovely stroke, created the room to swing his arms and timed it very well
four more, this is too wide and Williamson cuts hard past point, poor ball
fuller length, pushed through midwicket and they get back for a couple
good length on the stumps, blocked in the crease
touch fuller, worked to square leg
length ball, this time Guptill is giving himself room to slap over the off side, good strike
Guptill was going leg side again so Dernbach followed him and cramped him up, just blocked

atouch shorter and Guptill tries to pull, get it all wrong and pops up a catch to Jordan at midwicket. Right off the splice of the bat, it skidded on a bit quicker than Guptill was expecting and went almost straight up, Jordan coming to his right to take an easy catch
slower ball, a low full toss, just blocked
length and touched through square leg for an easy couple
length delivery just outside off, punched firmly to cover
full length just outside off, firmly driven to extra cover
goes to cut hard and misses outside off
skips down the wicket, Broad follows him with a full delivery at the pads but McCullum adjusts in a flash and slaps it over midwicket, outrageous stroke
goes for another swing and this takes a big top edge and flies over first slip, very fortunate
excellent yorker, dug out back to the bowler
low full toss and McCullum hammers it down the ground for six, big strike
full on the stumps and flicked out wide of midwicket, poor loosener
forward just outside off, blocked to point
